      An IRS audit is no different than a cop pulling you over for a broken taillight. Said cop/auditor is not interested in the taillight. He's a human with aspirations of greater things like bonuses and promotions and boondoggle travel revenue. Cop/auditor is there to poke indiscriminately into your life in order to find unknown goodies like drugs in the trunk or unreported revenues. The average JoeBlow taxpayer doesn't make enough mistakes to justify the invasion by the cop/auditor, but Congress will never know as any government agency worth its existence is going to cook the numbers knowing that only outside intervention by professionals will "find them out", but that won't happen as Congress won't pay to uncover the deceit...preferring to increase the budgets every year for these floundering agencies.<br/>IRS doesn't work....never did work fairly and needs serious reorganization starting with the discovery and removal of incompetent management. <br/><br/>YES! as with many government agencies, the scum at the bottom of the barrel breaks off, rises through the brilliant milk and settles at the top like the  spoiled cream that is management.<br/><br/>Like the blind pied piper leading the kids off the cliff, management in IRS joyfully leads and steps aside while the kids fall into the abyss.

                  
